[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Issue:** The voice is strong and consistent. The opening scenario ("a care manager has a panel of 200 patients with diabetes") is specific and grounded. The "Call too early... Call too late" parallel structure is effective without being gimmicky. "The question isn't who to call. She already knows who's struggling. The question is *when* to call." This is exactly the right register: direct, slightly urgent, engineer-explaining-a-hard-problem energy.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The Technology section maintains the teaching voice well. "Here's the fundamental difficulty: you want to know the optimal time to intervene, but you can only observe what actually happened" is a clean explanation of the counterfactual problem that a non-ML reader can follow.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m One minor observation: the sentence "This is where we're headed" at the end of The Problem section is slightly forward-looking/visionary in a way that borders on marketing. It works in context but is the closest the recipe gets to hype.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The "Honest Take" opening ("This is one of the hardest problems in healthcare ML, and I want to be upfront about that") is appropriately humble and sets the right expectations.
