[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Location:** Overall structure
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Issue:** The recipe follows the 70/30 split correctly. The Problem, The Technology, and General Architecture Pattern sections are entirely vendor-agnostic. AWS services appear only in "The AWS Implementation." The Technology section discusses survival analysis, hazard functions, RNNs, transformers, IPTW, and G-computation without mentioning any AWS service. A reader on GCP or Azure would learn the full conceptual framework.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The AWS section is proportionally appropriate and well-justified (each service choice is explained in "Why These Services").
