[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m #### FINDING V-4: Minor Doc-Voice Creep (Severity: LOW)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Location:** "Why These Services" section, Glue paragraph
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Issue:** "Glue's support for incremental processing matters here because patient timelines need daily updates, not full rebuilds." This sentence is fine but slightly more documentation-voice than the rest of the recipe. Compare with the more natural voice elsewhere: "This is the hardest engineering step in the entire pipeline." The Glue sentence reads like a feature description rather than an engineer explaining a choice.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Suggested Fix:** Optional rephrase: "Glue handles incremental processing, which matters because you're updating patient timelines daily, not rebuilding them from scratch." Minor; no action required if deemed acceptable.
